en_550350_0	Army Directorate of Preventive Medicine and Mental Health took steps to conduct a series of workshops, themed ‘How to Mitigate Mental Stress and Prevention of Suicide’ to educate all serving under the Security Force Headquarters - Kilinochchi (SFHQ-KLN) during 16 - 18 October.
en_550350_1	63 Officers and 1036 Soldiers of the SFHQ-KLN, Forward Maintenance Area - Kilinochchi (FMA-KLN) and All Divisional Headquarters on the instructions of Major General Niyshshanka Ranawana, Commander SFHQ-KLN attended the workshops.
en_550350_2	Lecturers at the Directorate of Preventive Medicine and Mental Health of the Sri Lanka Army and visiting lecturers at the Divisional Secretariats at Walipitiya, Akuressa and Ambalantota also supported the conduct of these lectures.
